<br>
What I do is root a mob, brutes are one of the best for this purpose. Than charm it. Since the pet can't move than i pull a mob back and get the pet on it if charm is still on.  Than you root the one you pulled and let them fight.  Your pet should win if you haste it, but the charmed one will be low on HP so you can usually finish it off in a nuke or two, than you do it again.  Once you are lvl 60 and have 27 aa points you can get Dire Charm, this is a great thing and you can solo much much easiar with it.  I have a few lvl 60 chanter friends with this, and the two of us soloed the arena area in kael for a couple hours easiar, and even help camp in UD in VL <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jedc>jedc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(8/21/02 1:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soloing a Chanter</span><hr size=1> I now have a almost 57 Chanter and I soloed him for a lot of his career.  The biggest challenge in soloing a chanter is making the most of you're abilities and picking WHERE to fight.  There aren't that many good chanter solo grounds...but when you find one...yes we can solo.<br>
<br>
For example, you can solo Uthorks in EW after 39 (even rhino's after 44) and this can take you all the way to 52.  The trick is to remember you're fear spell is as good as a necros and to know the fear path of the creatures you're going to pet kite.  Up in the north east corner of EW you just pull a mob to the tree on the coast (just north of the dorf villiage) allow it to hit you...back off and fear it...follow you're pet as it chews it up...(mob will always run south and there are NO adds along the path)....land a nuke or 2 as you can and re fear as required.  It's all by the numbers stuff and works.  To eliminate downtime for healing ALWAYS keep rune III up...don't underestimate the chanter pet as a damage dealer.  It can't take the hits but if you're fear kiting it doesn't have to and it's easily the equal of a necro pet in dealing damage AND when it does take hits it's the fastest healing pet in the game.<br>
<br>
You can do the same at the spiroc aviary in TD btw.<br>
<br>
If you don't want to do a chanter because they are hard to solo (and they are), you're best classes for soloing:<br>
<br>
Bard (BEST soloers in game in level range 27 to 55 bar none...any that say otherwise have never seen a good bard swarm kite...I have a 58 bard too...at 49 I was pulling the entire spiroc aviary in TD (12 to 14 mobs at once) and killing them all).  Bard will not kill 4 mobs as fast as a wiz or druid but has *0* down time until the early 50s and will kill 20 faster than they will kill 10.  A good bard can solo or get a group almost anywhere.  Check out EQDIVA.COM for more good info on bards.<br>
<br>
Druid or Wizard:  both about equal and awesome soloers.  Lots of down time if you dont' have access to clarity.  Quadkiting is the way to go here and starts at around level 34.  Neither class is high on the grouping list though in most places in the game from mid level on.<br>
<br>
Necro:  Solid soloer, little down time.  A necro kills one mob at a time...but very fast and has little down time when played well.  As with druid or wizard, necros have the problem of not being at the top of the group invite list.  Necro is one of the best soloers in the high end game (when it's a pain to solo with bards anymore).<br>
<br>
Jedc<br>
