<br>
To me it's not the issue of whether enchanters can solo, it's the issue of why bother?  I can walk in to Sebilis and have a group in 5 to 10 minutes.  I get random tells all the time about groups in CT.  Grouping is much faster exp for a chanter imho.  Any soloing I do is tradeskill farming really LOL.  <br>
<br>
IMHO a chanter needs to be played as a social class or grouping class because that appears to be our primary function.  We were designed basically as a buff enhancing class (haste and mana regenning) and a crowd controling class.  Enchanters aren't known for our dps.   Our pets -- not sure about them being = to necro pets on dammage -- dont' tank very efficiently at all and getting adds can be a nightmare (although far easier now that pets don't attack mezed mobs).<br>
<br>
Necromancers however appear to be a class designed to function well in solitude.  A great necro can be an amazing asset to a group, and even though they don't get dungeon groups often, they are high on my priority list when creating a group.  Necros can be main healer, mezer, and nuker if they play their mana pool right and if they know their class and have the right gear and spells.   One of my good friends is a damn good necro, and we can pretty much hold any camp in Seb just the two of us.  <br>
<br>
So in conclusion it depends how you want to play...do you want a class that is comfortable to solo with, and requires effort to group effectively....or do you want a class that is comfortable to group with (even down time waiting on groups is negligable) and requires effort to solo effectively.  Hard decision to make hehe....in the end I say make one of each and have fun =)<br>
<br>
<br>
Xaeviouran Orionne<br>
